(3) Standard Logical Key Setting Table

Although uum has 11 modes, this table shows them divided into 3 classes.
(Refer to the uumkey)

  (1) Reading Input Mode
    Keysym      (Command)| Function
    ---------------------+---------------------------------------------
    PF1                  | Switch between Hiragana and Katakana
    PF2 	         | Switch between full width and half width
    PF3                  | Switch between Romaji and direct input
    PF4                  | Switch to dictionary manipulation	
    Kanji            ^W  | Convert (large phrase)
                     ^Z  | Convert (small phrase)
    Execute	     ^L  | Confirm a conversion
    Right            ^F  | Move the cursor to the right
    Left 	     ^B  | Move the cursor to the left
    Down       	     ^N  | Next history
    Up      	     ^P  | Previous history 
    F11		     ^D  | Delete one character
    Meta + Right     ^E  | Move the cursor to the right end of the line 
    Meta + Left	     ^A  | Move the cursor to the left end of the line
    Meta + Up        ^K  | Delete from the cursor on
    Meta + F13       ^]  | Input Description Code
    Meta + F14   ^_  ^?  | Input JIS character codes
    F12	  	     ^U  | Recall 
    Meta + F11       ^T  | Registration function
        	     ^Y  | Output a string
                     ^C  | Un-convert 
  		     ^V  | Directly input the next character
